1
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:13,789
[Team Leader Baek Su Jeong]

2
00:00:13,790 --> 00:00:16,420
[Moon Ga Young]

3
00:00:17,790 --> 00:00:19,159
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

4
00:00:19,160 --> 00:00:22,009
[Choi Hyeon Wook]

5
00:00:22,010 --> 00:00:23,770
[Yongsung's successor. [The new chaebol director?]

6
00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:27,950
[Im Se Mi]

7
00:00:28,910 --> 00:00:30,920
[Kwak Shi Yang]

8
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:45,009
[My Dearest Enemy]

9
00:00:45,010 --> 00:00:47,619
[This series is fictional.]

10
00:00:47,620 --> 00:00:49,790
[Characters and settings are fictional.]

11
00:00:53,990 --> 00:00:55,770
What's this...

12
00:00:58,010 --> 00:01:00,030
like this?

13
00:01:04,850 --> 00:01:06,790
This...

14
00:01:08,970 --> 00:01:11,350
I gave it to my first love to confess my love.

15
00:01:12,220 --> 00:01:14,410
It has no other meaning.

16
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:18,139
I didn't want to forget the wound I sustained back then.

17
00:01:18,140 --> 00:01:20,710
That's why I hid it.

18
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:28,070
Or...

19
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:31,100
why are you asking...

20
00:01:34,090 --> 00:01:36,310
You're the Black Dragon, aren't you?

21
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:50,070
Strawberry?

22
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:58,710
Didn't you know it was me?

23
00:02:05,140 --> 00:02:07,979
I guess you didn't know.

24
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:11,190
That's why we're in this mess.

25
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:24,070
Go. I can't talk right now.

26
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:22,850
[Chapter 9]

27
00:03:26,420 --> 00:03:28,859
What if they find out who the other person is?

28
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:31,299
I'm sure that would be a huge shock.

29
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:36,019
Since they haven't found it yet, maybe they'll never know.

30
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:40,809
And Ju Yeon finally...

31
00:03:40,810 --> 00:03:43,050
He looks genuinely happy.

32
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,850
Oh.

33
00:04:06,610 --> 00:04:08,189
Ha Jin, are you busy at work?

34
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:09,469
Shall I come and help you?

35
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:12,000
You know I'm not busy.

36
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:16,639
Ha Jin, should I come and entertain you then?

37
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,339
Instead, you should rest.

38
00:04:18,340 --> 00:04:20,739
You must be tired of following my schedule.

39
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:22,729
I'm not tired at all.

40
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:24,699
Being at home is more tiring.

41
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:28,530
I have no energy because I can't see you.

42
00:04:29,620 --> 00:04:32,139
I actually want to talk about something.

43
00:04:32,140 --> 00:04:33,619
What?

44
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:36,320
Black Dragon and Su Jeong.

45
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,480
What about them?

46
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:53,509
Hey! Hey, beggar!

47
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:54,970
Hey!

48
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,740
Hey, how can a beggar ignore me?

49
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:16,050
This is your fault!

50
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,239
Yong Jun.

51
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:21,149
Are you alright? Oh, no...

52
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:23,420
Did you two have a fight?

53
00:05:25,150 --> 00:05:28,009
Don't you see he's injured? [Administrative Office]

54
00:05:28,010 --> 00:05:32,279
What will you do if there's a scar on your precious leg?

55
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,919
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

56
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,609
Do you think an apology is enough?

57
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:38,020
You need to raise your child well.

58
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:41,319
I heard that Su Jeong's mother is in the hospital.

59
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:44,019
I'm sorry about that too.

60
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:46,329
It must be difficult alone.

61
00:05:46,330 --> 00:05:47,429
But still.

62
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:50,960
You shouldn't completely neglect your child.

63
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:52,718
Sir?

64
00:05:52,730 --> 00:05:56,299
He is often reported to not bring materials and to disrupt classes.

65
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:59,069
I heard he couldn't pay for his lunch on time either.

66
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:03,449
Did you know that she didn't bring any food to the picnic and forced everyone to share?

67
00:06:03,450 --> 00:06:04,553
Lady.

68
00:06:04,565 --> 00:06:07,909
Other mothers complain that she spoils the classroom atmosphere.

69
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:10,270
And it created problems like that.

70
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:18,050
I am sorry.

71
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:20,960
Let's go, Yong Jun.

72
00:06:49,770 --> 00:06:51,129
Baba.

73
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:52,490
Yes.

74
00:06:53,130 --> 00:06:54,620
Ben...

75
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:58,269
I didn't.

76
00:06:58,270 --> 00:07:00,289
Yes.

77
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:03,539
I should pay more attention to you.

78
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:05,489
No.

79
00:07:05,490 --> 00:07:07,560
I am good.

80
00:07:08,460 --> 00:07:13,400
I decided to be strong on my own.

81
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:17,710
Darling!

82
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:23,819
No...

83
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:26,600
I decided to check out Baek Su Bin as well.

84
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:31,670
Because the father doesn't have the power to do it, and the mother...

85
00:07:32,290 --> 00:07:34,070
He's gone now.

86
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:38,149
Perhaps that's why I was even angrier.

87
00:07:38,150 --> 00:07:42,339
You were the first person I wanted to trust.

88
00:07:42,340 --> 00:07:47,580
But in the end, I couldn't trust you either.

89
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:51,160
And I have to be alone.

90
00:08:12,130 --> 00:08:16,619
I heard that this place is famous for its bagel sandwiches.

91
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:19,139
We are here because they wanted to join our store.

92
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:22,569
Does it taste bad?

93
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:25,770
No, it's fine.

94
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:32,709
Did something happen last night?

95
00:08:32,710 --> 00:08:34,769
You look tired.

96
00:08:34,770 --> 00:08:37,009
You don't seem to have any appetite either.

97
00:08:37,010 --> 00:08:40,830
Was there a problem with the room you stayed in?

98
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,249
I didn't sleep very well.

99
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:46,710
I had a nightmare.

100
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:53,080
It was about things that shouldn't have happened.

101
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:56,759
I still feel very alive, as if it were real.

102
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,470
Safe.

103
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:02,149
It must be a terrible nightmare.

104
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:04,409
[My Princess]

105
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:07,480
One moment, please.

106
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,289
I don't like these kinds of fashion styles.

107
00:09:34,290 --> 00:09:35,769
I don't even want to be near it.

108
00:09:35,770 --> 00:09:38,089
So what now?

109
00:09:38,090 --> 00:09:39,909
I don't care.

110
00:09:39,910 --> 00:09:42,380
Because I love you.

111
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:45,589
The character in the game isn't real.

112
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:47,499
Actually, you're such a pathetic person.

113
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:53,900
Stop pretending like that and stay sealed forever, you little cow!

114
00:09:55,620 --> 00:10:03,390
If the same person hurts me and also makes me smile, what should I do?

115
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:14,200
Hey, are you sick or something?

116
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,650
- Sister. - Yes.

117
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:24,139
Nothing. I'll wait for you to start.

118
00:10:24,140 --> 00:10:25,609
What did you want to say?

119
00:10:25,610 --> 00:10:27,000
What?

120
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:30,580
Thing...

121
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,420
Your director.

122
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:41,410
Do you still get along well with him/her?

123
00:10:42,110 --> 00:10:44,240
Why are you asking?

124
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:48,810
Well...

125
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,999
Y-So, the director...

126
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,929
Is the director Black Dragon?

127
00:10:54,930 --> 00:10:58,849
What? How—how did you know?

128
00:10:58,850 --> 00:11:00,670
Since when?

129
00:11:01,770 --> 00:11:03,810
Since last night.

130
00:11:07,110 --> 00:11:10,549
Did you really have to drag me out as soon as you got back from your business trip?

131
00:11:10,550 --> 00:11:12,479
Prepare yourself and listen.

132
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:16,680
Now we're going to my girlfriend's shop.

133
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:18,899
Why would I go there?

134
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:21,280
The name of the place is 'Sulo.'

135
00:11:22,170 --> 00:11:24,900
Is the owner of that place your girlfriend?

136
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:31,840
Yes. When we get there, your first love will be there.

137
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:35,590
Su Jeong?

138
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:39,500
Damn it.

139
00:11:43,210 --> 00:11:44,309
You knew?

140
00:11:44,310 --> 00:11:45,909
H-Since when?

141
00:11:45,910 --> 00:11:47,579
Since last night.

142
00:11:47,580 --> 00:11:49,959
Since last night.

143
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:52,209
Hey, are you okay?

144
00:11:52,210 --> 00:11:54,900
Shouldn't we go? Huh?

145
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:03,759
How long have you known?

146
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:09,960
I saw you two together on the day you brought the director.

147
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:13,919
Yes, it should have happened then.

148
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:16,259
I've thought about this a lot too.

149
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:19,289
I thought you'd be even more surprised to learn more later.

150
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:21,719
That's why I wanted to say it today.

151
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,990
Are you okay, Su Jeong?

152
00:12:24,730 --> 00:12:27,309
I am not ok.

153
00:12:27,310 --> 00:12:30,120
I'm not feeling well at all.

154
00:12:30,820 --> 00:12:32,699
You dated Black Dragon, right?

155
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:35,499
This is the downside.

156
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:38,329
How can the Black Dragon and I be together...?

157
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:40,889
Oh dear, why didn't I understand?

158
00:12:40,890 --> 00:12:42,579
You should have told me sooner.

159
00:12:42,580 --> 00:12:44,249
I wanted it.

160
00:12:44,250 --> 00:12:46,709
But I didn't want it to affect his work.

161
00:12:46,710 --> 00:12:49,500
And I really didn't know you were going to leave.

162
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:53,619
Yes.

163
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:55,989
It's not your fault at all.

164
00:12:55,990 --> 00:12:58,560
It's all my fault. My fault.

165
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:01,509
When I learned...

166
00:13:01,510 --> 00:13:05,189
Black Dragon was an immature middle school student.

167
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:09,268
More than being fooled by a child...

168
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:13,770
...what bothered me was that I wasn't sure what I loved about him.

169
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:19,119
The person I loved and trusted was fake, you know.

170
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:22,889
This time I thought I knew him well.

171
00:13:22,890 --> 00:13:28,549
If the Black Dragon is the one who deceived me, then who exactly did I fall in love with?

172
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:32,500
What are you going to do now?

173
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:39,760
I want to avoid him for now, but...

174
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,990
Hello.

175
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:53,209
Thing...

176
00:13:53,210 --> 00:13:56,080
I don't know what to say.

177
00:13:56,830 --> 00:13:59,070
But I thought I needed to see you.

178
00:14:01,930 --> 00:14:05,360
I wanted to see you. That's why I came.

179
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:16,795
So, you met by chance in the shop and in the game...

180
00:14:16,807 --> 00:14:21,139
...you learned that we are Black Dragon and Strawberry, who met.

181
00:14:21,140 --> 00:14:23,690
While they try to separate us

182
00:14:24,380 --> 00:14:25,709
Did you get together?

183
00:14:25,710 --> 00:14:28,399
We also met by chance.

184
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:32,959
We didn't come together while you were trying to separate us.

185
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:35,419
That's not the important thing here.

186
00:14:35,420 --> 00:14:40,169
That means the manager knows everything about my past.

187
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:42,489
C-Not much. D-I've learned a little.

188
00:14:42,490 --> 00:14:44,430
A little.

189
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:51,190
- I'm leaving. - Su Jeong!

190
00:14:52,010 --> 00:14:54,929
Wait, calm down a bit.

191
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:56,719
Can you sit down for a minute?

192
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:58,470
Shall we sit down?

193
00:15:06,990 --> 00:15:11,659
E-If you don't mind, may I say something?

194
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:15,249
Since this has happened, I want all four of us to come to an agreement.

195
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:18,059
Let's leave the past in the past.

196
00:15:18,060 --> 00:15:21,670
And this happened when I was little.

197
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:27,559
You two will continue to see each other, right?

198
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,510
- Yes. - No.

199
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:37,649
Safe.

200
00:15:37,650 --> 00:15:39,459
I need to start preparing for today.

201
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:43,670
Oh dear, I should help him too.

202
00:15:50,620 --> 00:15:53,040
Let's talk outside.

203
00:15:54,950 --> 00:15:56,950
- Wait- - Su Jeong-

204
00:15:57,910 --> 00:15:59,600
- Ju Yeon- - Kara Ejder-

205
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:09,390
Sence...

206
00:16:10,290 --> 00:16:13,150
Can you continue to love me?

207
00:16:14,020 --> 00:16:16,539
What do you want to say?

208
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:19,690
You've found out who I am.

209
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:23,770
Can you still love me?

210
00:16:27,910 --> 00:16:29,990
Sence...

211
00:16:33,050 --> 00:16:35,280
Can't you do it?

212
00:16:41,490 --> 00:16:43,930
I think it will be difficult.

213
00:16:47,390 --> 00:16:49,669
I don't think I can.

214
00:16:49,670 --> 00:16:51,719
Can you make this decision so easily?

215
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:54,799
It's not easy. Obviously.

216
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:59,680
No matter how much I thought about it, my answer would be the same.

217
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:07,450
- Mrs. Baek - Well, let's finish now.

218
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:12,520
Now to finish...

219
00:17:13,210 --> 00:17:15,720
It would be best for both of us.

220
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:22,050
What do you think happened to them?

221
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:27,629
Ju Yeon wants to keep seeing him, but Su Jeong doesn't.

222
00:18:27,630 --> 00:18:31,660
Perhaps they've been hurt more by the past than we think.

223
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:37,855
Rather, if you keep bumping into a wall, the wall...

224
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:43,069
...you're good at breaking things, but you know the wall very well.

225
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:45,639
This can amplify your fear.

226
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:52,439
Su Jeong often found himself alone, hitting many different walls.

227
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:56,000
They might not want to deal with a particular wall.

228
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:02,440
I don't think he wants to bring the pain up again.

229
00:19:21,810 --> 00:19:25,460
[Su Jeong]

230
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:56,840
So let's finish now.

231
00:19:57,680 --> 00:20:00,410
Now to finish...

232
00:20:01,110 --> 00:20:03,560
It would be best for both of us.

233
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:09,130
It was easy for him.

234
00:21:19,210 --> 00:21:21,360
Team Leader Baek.

235
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:31,630
Come to my office immediately.

236
00:21:46,130 --> 00:21:48,339
Please...

237
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:50,360
Sit and wait.

238
00:22:29,730 --> 00:22:31,730
Team Leader Baek.

239
00:22:34,280 --> 00:22:35,810
Yes.

240
00:22:36,810 --> 00:22:40,809
The next branch to be renovated should be the Daejeon branch.

241
00:22:40,810 --> 00:22:43,869
The audit results also look good.

242
00:22:43,870 --> 00:22:47,629
I will prepare it in a way that will not affect the program.

243
00:22:47,630 --> 00:22:50,200
I haven't told you to leave yet.

244
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,810
Wait.

245
00:22:55,380 --> 00:22:57,640
Our conversation isn't over.

246
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:30,800
Director, why are you making me sit here all day?

247
00:23:37,690 --> 00:23:38,949
I told you. I need to talk to you.

248
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:41,569
Then speak now.

249
00:23:41,570 --> 00:23:45,090
Just because we broke up—that's your opinion.

250
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:48,379
I can't leave.

251
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:51,099
Why should we break up?

252
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:53,410
Do you have to ask?

253
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:58,929
Have you forgotten what first love meant to us?

254
00:23:58,930 --> 00:24:00,829
A bad memory.

255
00:24:00,830 --> 00:24:04,400
We don't want to be reminded. How can we continue the conversation?

256
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:09,080
Because I still love you.

257
00:24:10,380 --> 00:24:13,019
You told me to keep loving what I love.

258
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:15,460
That's you.

259
00:24:17,620 --> 00:24:19,910
How can I stand?

260
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:25,870
You said you loved me too.

261
00:24:27,450 --> 00:24:30,820
That was a time when I didn't know who he was.

262
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:45,530
In that case...

263
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:49,510
I won't tell you my age...

264
00:24:51,080 --> 00:24:52,890
I am sorry.

265
00:24:54,180 --> 00:24:56,370
It was my fault.

266
00:24:57,270 --> 00:24:58,850
Please...

267
00:24:59,930 --> 00:25:01,699
Please forgive me.

268
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,770
Forget everything...

269
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:09,200
And think about Ban Ju Yeon now.

270
00:25:17,270 --> 00:25:19,050
From where...

271
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:23,490
You haven't changed at all?

272
00:25:25,990 --> 00:25:28,579
You were like that back then too.

273
00:25:28,580 --> 00:25:30,999
You said you loved me.

274
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:34,600
But you left me behind, as if it was all a lie.

275
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:44,680
Have you seen?

276
00:25:45,270 --> 00:25:48,260
You haven't forgotten that I hurt you.

277
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:52,840
As you said,

278
00:25:54,220 --> 00:25:59,050
I wish my love for you was a complete lie and a joke.

279
00:25:59,950 --> 00:26:05,909
I wouldn't be hurt, and I wouldn't say things that would hurt a child.

280
00:26:05,910 --> 00:26:11,120
I could have comforted you by saying we could meet again when we're older.

281
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:14,300
I truly loved you.

282
00:26:16,250 --> 00:26:18,399
I trusted you this much.

283
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:21,680
I was happy to have someone I could trust.

284
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:30,850
But you were just a child.

285
00:26:38,270 --> 00:26:41,030
How can I ever love you again now?

286
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:25,260
I made it very spicy.

287
00:27:39,380 --> 00:27:41,419
How did it happen?

288
00:27:41,420 --> 00:27:44,819
I can't say if it's painful or not.

289
00:27:44,820 --> 00:27:47,740
How strange. It can't be.

290
00:27:52,660 --> 00:27:54,860
I broke up with him.

291
00:27:59,980 --> 00:28:03,080
You don't open up easily.

292
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:06,850
You must have loved him very much.

293
00:28:08,290 --> 00:28:10,150
I know.

294
00:28:11,730 --> 00:28:14,640
I think I was very lonely.

295
00:28:20,760 --> 00:28:23,260
After meeting with the Black Dragon...

296
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:27,210
During the offline meeting, I realized that...

297
00:28:30,610 --> 00:28:33,820
I was truly alone.

298
00:28:34,990 --> 00:28:37,360
I was desperate.

299
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:43,770
I needed someone so much...

300
00:28:44,690 --> 00:28:47,250
I didn't realize he was a child.

301
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:54,730
I think that's why I was deceived.

302
00:28:55,830 --> 00:28:57,780
Like an idiot.

303
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,660
I hate this so much.

304
00:29:04,030 --> 00:29:07,090
You don't just hate the Black Dragon.

305
00:29:10,380 --> 00:29:12,879
You hate yourself too.

306
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:14,990
From the person he was then.

307
00:29:29,610 --> 00:29:31,200
Elder brother,

308
00:29:32,460 --> 00:29:35,209
Have you ever experienced a breakup?

309
00:29:35,210 --> 00:29:36,590
What?

310
00:29:38,950 --> 00:29:42,400
You've experienced it many times because you've gone out so much.

311
00:29:43,780 --> 00:29:49,110
How could you relive so much heartbreak?

312
00:29:50,550 --> 00:29:52,279
Ju Yeon, I think you're drunk.

313
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:58,119
When dating, both people need to agree.

314
00:29:58,120 --> 00:29:59,599
But why?

315
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:03,050
Why in the end, one person,

316
00:30:03,890 --> 00:30:06,549
Does it end when you say 'it's over'?

317
00:30:06,550 --> 00:30:08,029
I disagree with this.

318
00:30:08,030 --> 00:30:13,490
Ben, Ban Ju Yeon, bu...

319
00:30:14,220 --> 00:30:17,090
I will fight against the brutal system of segregation.

320
00:30:25,900 --> 00:30:27,480
No.

321
00:30:30,430 --> 00:30:33,079
Actually, I can't.

322
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:35,739
Because I don't have the right.

323
00:30:35,740 --> 00:30:36,939
What do you mean by "right"?

324
00:30:36,940 --> 00:30:39,590
I thought I was the only one suffering...

325
00:30:42,350 --> 00:30:44,729
Because I was the only one being sincere.

326
00:30:44,730 --> 00:30:47,850
How disappointed she was in me...

327
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:54,450
And I didn't know how hurt she was, thinking she had been deceived.

328
00:30:56,620 --> 00:30:59,980
I was a truly ignorant child.

329
00:31:00,660 --> 00:31:04,650
I'm the one who hurts her the most.

330
00:31:07,310 --> 00:31:08,960
Ju-Yeon.

331
00:31:13,570 --> 00:31:15,230
Git.

332
00:31:35,740 --> 00:31:38,540
The person I truly hate...

333
00:31:40,210 --> 00:31:42,230
It wasn't you.

334
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:46,780
It was me.

335
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:24,609
[Is Yongsung's heir, Ban Ju Yeon, getting married?]

336
00:32:24,610 --> 00:32:26,399
An employee?

337
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,779
That's what a team leader says, according to a rumor.

338
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:30,549
[Is she dating a subordinate, not a chaebol?]

339
00:32:30,550 --> 00:32:31,749
- Look. - Seriously...

340
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:33,019
Behind.

341
00:32:33,020 --> 00:32:37,139
Team Leader, did you see this by chance?

342
00:32:37,140 --> 00:32:39,629
[Is Yongsung's heir, Ban Ju Yeon, getting married?]

343
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,029
What's this?

344
00:32:41,030 --> 00:32:43,960
I also saw the original photo.

345
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:48,800
I believe this woman is Baek Su Jeong from the Strategy Team.

346
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:07,589
There was an article on an office workers' website this morning.

347
00:33:07,590 --> 00:33:10,199
I think that's where it started. [I saw a chaebol]

348
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:13,440
You were recently announced as the heir and some...

349
00:33:13,452 --> 00:33:17,409
...even the employees recognized Team Leader Baek in the photo.

350
00:33:17,410 --> 00:33:24,129
Even before the PR team could handle it, it had already spread across various social media platforms and websites.

351
00:33:24,130 --> 00:33:26,850
During this process, the rumor grew.

352
00:33:27,490 --> 00:33:29,250
I understand.

353
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:34,669
Why did you meet Team Leader Baek's family?

354
00:33:34,670 --> 00:33:36,209
I met them.

355
00:33:36,210 --> 00:33:39,459
And to be polite, I bought them a meal.

356
00:33:39,460 --> 00:33:40,859
I understand.

357
00:33:40,860 --> 00:33:43,969
I thought so too.

358
00:33:43,970 --> 00:33:47,439
You're in a difficult situation for no reason.

359
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:49,049
I know.

360
00:33:49,050 --> 00:33:51,090
How unfair to Mrs. Baek.

361
00:33:54,970 --> 00:33:57,310
Get it done as soon as possible.

362
00:34:11,570 --> 00:34:14,999
Team Leader Baek, I heard you're marrying the director.

363
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,839
- Is that true? - Excuse me?

364
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:20,029
I heard your wedding will be at the Yongsung Hotel.

365
00:34:20,030 --> 00:34:22,419
The hotel staff know everything.

366
00:34:22,420 --> 00:34:25,619
But why would the director date Team Leader Baek?

367
00:34:25,620 --> 00:34:26,749
And should she even marry him?

368
00:34:26,750 --> 00:34:29,389
Why not? It's beautiful.

369
00:34:29,390 --> 00:34:30,599
Yes.

370
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:32,089
Being beautiful is the best.

371
00:34:32,090 --> 00:34:35,370
Oh, I wish I were beautiful too.

372
00:34:37,460 --> 00:34:39,670
Excuse me, team leaders,

373
00:34:40,270 --> 00:34:43,409
I thought Yongsung Store was number one in the industry.

374
00:34:43,410 --> 00:34:45,749
That's why I was proud to work here.

375
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,119
I did my best too.

376
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:51,134
But the team leaders at store number 1 are responding to an unconfirmed rumor...

377
00:34:51,146 --> 00:34:54,539
...he believes and judges a female colleague's appearance.

378
00:34:54,540 --> 00:34:55,769
I'm disappointed.

379
00:34:55,770 --> 00:34:58,470
We were complimenting you.

380
00:35:09,500 --> 00:35:11,360
Let's begin the meeting.

381
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:14,130
Ve...

382
00:35:16,270 --> 00:35:18,840
Let's only talk about work in the office.

383
00:35:36,770 --> 00:35:40,769
I know what you're thinking, but the director and I aren't.

384
00:35:40,770 --> 00:35:43,030
Yes. Of course you're not.

385
00:35:43,850 --> 00:35:45,310
Sir?

386
00:35:48,340 --> 00:35:51,219
Na Na, what's wrong? Is something wrong?

387
00:35:51,220 --> 00:35:53,349
That's not true.

388
00:35:53,350 --> 00:35:56,199
No, just...

389
00:35:56,200 --> 00:36:00,429
I thought you might find this very unfair.

390
00:36:00,430 --> 00:36:03,359
- Excuse me? - That makes no sense.

391
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:04,889
Why you...?

392
00:36:04,890 --> 00:36:08,159
So you're going to jump into hell even with the director?

393
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:11,399
Really. They know nothing.

394
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:13,179
Absolutely impossible.

395
00:36:13,180 --> 00:36:17,019
But people are speaking very badly.

396
00:36:17,020 --> 00:36:20,059
Because they couldn't see how much they hated each other.

397
00:36:20,060 --> 00:36:22,729
They were terrifying on the roof.

398
00:36:22,730 --> 00:36:26,410
You should be upset about all this nonsense.

399
00:36:27,060 --> 00:36:29,089
I am good.

400
00:36:29,090 --> 00:36:32,029
- Don't cry, Na Na. - Team Leader...

401
00:36:32,030 --> 00:36:34,266
I know. To entertain themselves...

402
00:36:34,278 --> 00:36:36,919
...they believe whatever they want to believe. Do you understand?

403
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:38,619
They know how to fabricate sensational things.

404
00:36:38,620 --> 00:36:40,559
They have no idea what the Team Leader is like.

405
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:42,329
How much longer will this go on?

406
00:36:42,330 --> 00:36:43,759
I don't know.

407
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:46,179
It's a false rumor. They'll stop talking within a month.

408
00:36:46,180 --> 00:36:48,920
Yes. They should be.

409
00:36:50,570 --> 00:36:53,080
I'm going to report them.

410
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:56,969
I removed all the articles.

411
00:36:56,970 --> 00:36:59,919
We decided not to address it formally.

412
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:03,669
The PR team is analyzing public opinion in online communities.

413
00:37:03,670 --> 00:37:05,970
They say it's a baseless rumor.

414
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:14,729
Many didn't believe it, thinking the heirs and employees couldn't get out.

415
00:37:14,730 --> 00:37:18,030
I think everything will calm down in time.

416
00:37:27,100 --> 00:37:29,599
You wanted to see me, Madam President.

417
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:31,170
Yes.

418
00:37:32,230 --> 00:37:37,089
I'm not interested in your game, but knowing about family activities is enough.

419
00:37:37,090 --> 00:37:40,739
Why are you creating noise by not recognizing the hierarchy?

420
00:37:40,740 --> 00:37:43,339
You're giving people the wrong impression.

421
00:37:43,340 --> 00:37:48,489
- Extremism always creates problems. - I'm sorry.

422
00:37:48,490 --> 00:37:53,629
Because you are known as the heir, wherever you go and whoever you are with...

423
00:37:53,641 --> 00:37:58,369
...if you meet up, do so, but don't forget that investors are watching you.

424
00:37:58,370 --> 00:38:04,709
If you want to grow the company, meet the right people in the right places.

425
00:38:04,710 --> 00:38:07,339
Yes, I'll keep that in mind.

426
00:38:07,340 --> 00:38:09,569
Alright...

427
00:38:09,570 --> 00:38:12,019
Are you just going to leave it like this?

428
00:38:12,020 --> 00:38:14,649
They started talking even though there was nothing there.

429
00:38:14,650 --> 00:38:17,109
Do you think this won't happen again?

430
00:38:17,110 --> 00:38:21,599
Next time, they'll make a fuss over even smaller things.

431
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:23,639
Baek Su Jeong...

432
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:28,980
Find the right moment and fire him before people notice.

433
00:38:30,640 --> 00:38:35,550
You need to pull the weed out from the very beginning.

434
00:38:37,920 --> 00:38:40,270
I think this will be difficult.

435
00:38:43,820 --> 00:38:46,279
Will it be difficult?

436
00:38:46,280 --> 00:38:48,360
Team Leader Baek...

437
00:38:49,570 --> 00:38:52,789
This is a very important piece of staff for the renovation project.

438
00:38:52,790 --> 00:38:55,814
Dismissing him because of a false rumor is a significant...

439
00:38:55,826 --> 00:38:58,709
...it would be our loss if we were faced with that project.

440
00:38:58,710 --> 00:39:01,570
It would be difficult to replace him.

441
00:39:14,270 --> 00:39:16,020
Okay.

442
00:39:17,530 --> 00:39:19,590
Then leave him.

443
00:39:20,660 --> 00:39:26,300
If he comes back on my radar, I'll take action myself.

444
00:39:27,690 --> 00:39:29,340
You can go.

445
00:39:39,650 --> 00:39:42,269
Their...

446
00:39:42,270 --> 00:39:45,229
You knew how to bring them together, didn't you, Manager Kwon?

447
00:39:45,230 --> 00:39:47,489
Yes, I knew it.

448
00:39:47,490 --> 00:39:48,549
Or...

449
00:39:48,550 --> 00:39:52,179
You have also dealt with the families of employees in the past.

450
00:39:52,180 --> 00:39:53,939
I didn't think this would be a problem.

451
00:39:53,940 --> 00:39:55,899
That's why I didn't tell you.

452
00:39:55,900 --> 00:39:58,279
I am sorry.

453
00:39:58,280 --> 00:40:03,750
If you're upset, you need to take responsibility, Manager Kwon.

454
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:19,739
Are you ok?

455
00:40:19,740 --> 00:40:23,149
Everyone's talking about the two of you all day.

456
00:40:23,150 --> 00:40:24,899
Why shouldn't I be okay?

457
00:40:24,900 --> 00:40:27,400
It's not true anyway.

458
00:40:32,500 --> 00:40:34,790
I didn't see...

459
00:40:39,330 --> 00:40:42,410
He's been in the Director's office for a while now.

460
00:40:44,110 --> 00:40:47,409
He was probably summoned by the president.

461
00:40:47,410 --> 00:40:48,539
He'll be fine.

462
00:40:48,540 --> 00:40:50,989
He's good at figuring everything out.

463
00:40:50,990 --> 00:40:53,310
You don't need to worry.

464
00:40:54,930 --> 00:40:57,020
I'm not worried.

465
00:41:01,940 --> 00:41:04,690
I think he's worried.

466
00:41:06,190 --> 00:41:10,319
I'm going to do something for all businesses whose sales record is below 10%.

467
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:12,309
- All of them? - Yes.

468
00:41:12,310 --> 00:41:15,079
We will either cancel the contract or come up with a plan.

469
00:41:15,080 --> 00:41:17,229
I plan to do things quickly.

470
00:41:17,230 --> 00:41:20,269
The renovation project is also ongoing.

471
00:41:20,270 --> 00:41:22,683
I don't know how it will turn out in the long term, but...

472
00:41:22,695 --> 00:41:25,449
...fixing a few large stores won't be enough.

473
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:28,754
To double sales and maybe even more...

474
00:41:28,766 --> 00:41:32,210
...for this reason, all branches need to improve their sales.

475
00:41:33,490 --> 00:41:34,799
We'll be busy.

476
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:37,769
We need to be even busier.

477
00:41:37,770 --> 00:41:39,149
That sounds good.

478
00:41:39,150 --> 00:41:43,090
We need to be very careful right now.

479
00:42:01,980 --> 00:42:03,890
Director.

480
00:42:08,760 --> 00:42:10,720
What's wrong?

481
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:13,709
Thing...

482
00:42:13,710 --> 00:42:18,079
This doesn't cause any problems with the lady president, does it?

483
00:42:18,080 --> 00:42:21,320
I don't think this concerns you.

484
00:42:22,250 --> 00:42:24,899
I'm directly involved. How can I not be worried?

485
00:42:24,900 --> 00:42:28,249
If he misunderstood, I'll explain myself.

486
00:42:28,250 --> 00:42:32,609
I'll say nothing happened—No. There's no need for that.

487
00:42:32,610 --> 00:42:34,869
Like you said, there's nothing.

488
00:42:34,870 --> 00:42:37,220
This won't be a problem.

489
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:40,859
Then I felt relieved.

490
00:42:40,860 --> 00:42:42,189
Yes like that.

491
00:42:42,190 --> 00:42:46,270
So, let's not get involved personally from now on.

492
00:42:48,210 --> 00:42:49,829
Okay.

493
00:42:49,830 --> 00:42:51,530
Finally...

494
00:42:52,190 --> 00:42:55,470
Everything seems to have returned to normal.

495
00:42:56,690 --> 00:42:58,580
Relaxing.

496
00:43:38,570 --> 00:43:40,899
The song is innocent.

497
00:43:40,900 --> 00:43:44,100
Start loving him again, together with me.

498
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:54,499
Payment has been processed.

499
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:56,029
Lady?

500
00:43:56,030 --> 00:43:57,689
Oh, yes.

501
00:43:57,690 --> 00:43:59,690
Thank you. Have a good day.

502
00:44:39,470 --> 00:44:42,770
I don't need to ask to do that, do I?

503
00:45:00,410 --> 00:45:02,409
Are you home, my daughter?

504
00:45:02,410 --> 00:45:06,160
Oh dear, why is it raining so much?

505
00:45:08,890 --> 00:45:10,820
Su Jeong.

506
00:45:18,440 --> 00:45:20,339
Baba.

507
00:45:20,340 --> 00:45:22,189
What's wrong, Su Jeong?

508
00:45:22,190 --> 00:45:24,409
Su Jeong, what is this?

509
00:45:24,410 --> 00:45:25,909
What's happening?

510
00:45:25,910 --> 00:45:28,430
I'm sorry, Dad.

511
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:34,579
I guess I wasn't such a strong person after all.

512
00:45:34,580 --> 00:45:37,870
I thought I was strong.

513
00:45:40,390 --> 00:45:42,850
What's wrong...

514
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:52,559
Sister, is it because of that jerk?

515
00:45:52,560 --> 00:45:54,359
Why? He wanted to keep it a secret.

516
00:45:54,360 --> 00:45:56,859
Is he blaming you for the rumor now?

517
00:45:56,860 --> 00:45:59,239
I'm going to kill that dog.

518
00:45:59,240 --> 00:46:01,879
No, that's not it. That's not it.

519
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:03,949
How is that not the case?

520
00:46:03,950 --> 00:46:06,119
Ben...

521
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:08,990
I suggested they leave.

522
00:46:09,930 --> 00:46:12,710
I left him, Dad.

523
00:46:51,110 --> 00:46:53,400
We decided to end it.

524
00:47:13,520 --> 00:47:16,103
When monitoring businesses with low sales,

525
00:47:16,115 --> 00:47:18,769
I noticed one of them stood out.

526
00:47:18,770 --> 00:47:21,299
Are you talking about the clothing brand 'Bukayo'?

527
00:47:21,300 --> 00:47:22,890
Yes.

528
00:47:33,640 --> 00:47:36,319
It's one of the bestsellers at another branch.

529
00:47:36,320 --> 00:47:37,799
The discrepancy was extreme.

530
00:47:37,800 --> 00:47:39,919
I'll just prepare a report about him.

531
00:47:39,920 --> 00:47:41,509
Send it this morning.

532
00:47:41,510 --> 00:47:43,569
Don't force me to ask you next time.

533
00:47:43,570 --> 00:47:46,340
Okay, I'll be more careful.

534
00:48:00,700 --> 00:48:01,999
Team Leader.

535
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:06,000
I think the rumor will disappear very soon.

536
00:48:06,880 --> 00:48:08,819
You seem more distant than before.

537
00:48:08,820 --> 00:48:11,990
The rumors didn't make things any stranger, did they?

538
00:48:12,830 --> 00:48:15,020
- No. - Right?

539
00:48:15,740 --> 00:48:17,800
That's good then.

540
00:48:19,670 --> 00:48:21,499
This is great.

541
00:48:21,500 --> 00:48:23,570
We don't seem close.

542
00:48:25,030 --> 00:48:26,800
[Grace]

543
00:48:30,820 --> 00:48:31,820
[Curved]

544
00:48:39,880 --> 00:48:41,730
Ok.

545
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:48,029
Come on, I told you to sit down.

546
00:48:48,030 --> 00:48:49,519
You make me feel bad.

547
00:48:49,520 --> 00:48:50,959
No problem.

548
00:48:50,960 --> 00:48:55,999
I'd rather be like this, close to you, than sit down.

549
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:57,950
Thank you.

550
00:49:00,990 --> 00:49:03,380
How is the Black Dragon?

551
00:49:04,750 --> 00:49:06,819
He's only focused on work.

552
00:49:06,820 --> 00:49:09,649
I think he's exaggerating, but that's just the way he is.

553
00:49:09,650 --> 00:49:12,179
I can't say whether it's worse or better.

554
00:49:12,180 --> 00:49:14,080
But I'm worried.

555
00:49:14,770 --> 00:49:16,489
Su Jeong too.

556
00:49:16,490 --> 00:49:18,229
He has always been focused on his work.

557
00:49:18,230 --> 00:49:21,419
Rumors spread when things were already complicated.

558
00:49:21,420 --> 00:49:23,909
They can't make progress overnight.

559
00:49:23,910 --> 00:49:25,549
It should disturb them.

560
00:49:25,550 --> 00:49:27,900
Even if they can't show it.

561
00:49:34,010 --> 00:49:36,619
Aren't you going home, Team Leader?

562
00:49:36,620 --> 00:49:37,889
I have to go.

563
00:49:37,890 --> 00:49:40,229
I'll be leaving soon. Don't worry and go now.

564
00:49:40,230 --> 00:49:41,949
Okay. See you tomorrow then.

565
00:49:41,950 --> 00:49:43,920
- Have a safe trip home. - Thank you.

566
00:51:12,960 --> 00:51:14,430
Team Leader.

567
00:51:33,240 --> 00:51:34,620
Director.

568
00:52:25,970 --> 00:52:30,000
Are you really relieved to be back to normal?

569
00:53:08,530 --> 00:53:11,199
Has anyone seen the director today?

570
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:12,699
No, I haven't seen it.

571
00:53:12,700 --> 00:53:14,239
Isn't he in his office?

572
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:15,909
He went home very late last night.

573
00:53:15,910 --> 00:53:19,169
I left after 10 o'clock, but he was still there.

574
00:53:19,170 --> 00:53:20,309
Really?

575
00:53:20,310 --> 00:53:21,709
One minute.

576
00:53:21,710 --> 00:53:25,509
He always keeps the messaging app open.

577
00:53:25,510 --> 00:53:27,129
Closed.

578
00:53:27,130 --> 00:53:29,059
At the meeting?

579
00:53:29,060 --> 00:53:32,030
How strange. It always keeps it on.

580
00:53:34,100 --> 00:53:35,980
[Director Ban Ju Yeon - Offline]

581
00:53:49,390 --> 00:53:51,670
Are you ok?

582
00:53:54,630 --> 00:53:57,690
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

583
00:54:01,490 --> 00:54:04,710
I need to get approval today.

584
00:54:10,890 --> 00:54:12,810
Manager.

585
00:54:14,540 --> 00:54:17,019
Is the director working remotely?

586
00:54:17,020 --> 00:54:20,649
He couldn't come today because he's sick.

587
00:54:20,650 --> 00:54:22,359
Is he/she very ill?

588
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:25,989
I'm not sure. I also received a brief report.

589
00:54:25,990 --> 00:54:27,899
If he could have come, he would have.

590
00:54:27,900 --> 00:54:31,759
Since he's at home, he must be very ill.

591
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:34,639
I'm worried. How sick is he/she?

592
00:54:34,640 --> 00:54:36,869
He had been skipping meals lately.

593
00:54:36,870 --> 00:54:39,089
He was working day and night.

594
00:54:39,090 --> 00:54:41,719
How can it be good?

595
00:54:41,720 --> 00:54:44,779
The president will be upset if she finds out.

596
00:54:44,780 --> 00:54:48,030
Will she be upset because he's sick?

597
00:54:49,250 --> 00:54:53,640
Health problems within the homeowner's family pose risks.

598
00:54:54,390 --> 00:54:56,400
Then, if you'll excuse me.

599
00:55:55,590 --> 00:55:58,980
Wake up. Why should you be the one worrying?

600
00:56:00,220 --> 00:56:04,190
But as a human being, I can worry about another human being.

601
00:56:07,620 --> 00:56:09,849
He's an adult. He'll figure it out himself.

602
00:56:09,850 --> 00:56:11,019
I'm sure it's fine.

603
00:56:11,020 --> 00:56:12,579
Will you be alright?

604
00:56:12,580 --> 00:56:15,936
Our relationship could be revealed at any moment, and that...

605
00:56:15,948 --> 00:56:20,219
Becoming Yongsung's successor could be a problem for your dream.

606
00:56:20,220 --> 00:56:24,480
I think I'll be alright...

607
00:56:25,280 --> 00:56:27,820
As long as I have you.

608
00:56:29,020 --> 00:56:31,930
As long as you love me.

609
00:56:40,180 --> 00:56:43,299
Medicine... Give me everything.

610
00:56:43,300 --> 00:56:46,059
He's not eating. He fainted from overwork.

611
00:56:46,060 --> 00:56:48,289
Give me everything I can to save him.

612
00:56:48,290 --> 00:56:50,270
[Pharmacy]

613
00:57:10,380 --> 00:57:12,640
Yes, Madam President.

614
00:57:17,310 --> 00:57:19,290
Director.

615
00:57:20,460 --> 00:57:21,999
My god.

616
00:57:22,000 --> 00:57:24,500
Director, are you alright?

617
00:57:41,800 --> 00:57:44,680
Did she try to go to work in that condition?

618
00:57:51,080 --> 00:57:53,040
I am sorry.

619
00:57:55,560 --> 00:58:00,270
I was sad then, and I'm sad now.

620
00:58:01,200 --> 00:58:04,840
I only thought about my own pain.

621
00:58:05,770 --> 00:58:09,650
I've forgotten the pain I caused.

622
00:58:10,850 --> 00:58:13,790
But it's the same this time too.

623
00:58:18,920 --> 00:58:22,340
What if I hurt him again?

624
00:58:27,770 --> 00:58:30,450
I want to be...

625
00:58:31,870 --> 00:58:35,350
I was going to be your biggest and coolest secret.

626
00:59:00,780 --> 00:59:02,730
Don't go.

627
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:18,950
Ben...

628
00:59:20,670 --> 00:59:24,830
I thought I wanted someone to love me.

629
00:59:26,180 --> 00:59:31,250
Even if I don't work for it or try very hard for it.

630
00:59:35,370 --> 00:59:37,430
Or...

631
00:59:40,250 --> 00:59:42,999
You gave me such love.

632
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:44,890
In that case...

633
00:59:46,630 --> 00:59:48,510
And now.

634
00:59:51,690 --> 00:59:54,410
So, don't feel bad about it.

635
00:59:55,870 --> 00:59:58,299
Don't hate yourself either.

636
00:59:58,300 --> 01:00:00,540
You already...

637
01:00:05,290 --> 01:00:08,650
You're my biggest and coolest secret.

638
01:00:11,200 --> 01:00:13,460
Because you are my first love.

639
01:00:31,240 --> 01:00:33,070
I love you.

640
01:00:46,110 --> 01:00:48,190
I love you too.

641
01:02:34,540 --> 01:02:35,710
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

642
01:02:41,240 --> 01:02:43,690
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

643
01:02:53,030 --> 01:02:55,419
[Notice of Termination]

644
01:02:55,420 --> 01:02:58,339
[Strategy Team Director Ban Ju Yeon]

645
01:02:58,340 --> 01:03:01,940
[My Dearest Enemy]

646
01:03:29,530 --> 01:03:33,149
Mrs. Baek was seen going in and out of the director's house...

647
01:03:33,150 --> 01:03:34,579
Was the director fired?

648
01:03:34,580 --> 01:03:36,489
Then you are unemployed.

649
01:03:36,490 --> 01:03:37,450
Unemployed?

650
01:03:37,451 --> 01:03:39,679
I'm bad at being bad at things.

651
01:03:39,680 --> 01:03:41,459
Things you do alone...

652
01:03:41,460 --> 01:03:43,219
Do it with me from now on.

653
01:03:43,220 --> 01:03:44,739
Team Leader Baek Su Jeong...

654
01:03:44,740 --> 01:03:46,169
Take care of her secretly.

655
01:03:46,170 --> 01:03:47,309
What is this, Team Leader?

656
01:03:47,310 --> 01:03:49,129
This makes no sense.

657
01:03:49,130 --> 01:03:53,229
Can you leave it up to the director for now?

658
01:03:53,230 --> 01:03:55,600
I will also have a choice to make.